        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-07-17T07:37:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it might be worthwhile to return an error status/flag here, so that the caller can safely abort the emulator if the resize didn\u0027t happen properly (e.g. out of disk space).\n\nCan you specify if there are specific constraints on the value of |newSize| as well as the size of the new partition file? E.g. I remember that ext4 partition sizes must be a multiple of 128MB or some other large granular size. I would assume it is then important to retrieve the size of the new partition to properly setup NAND emulation after that.",
      "revId": "c2a427efad4aa54635954f8feb54be2ad715bc0a",
